Indian silver leaps near close but gold becalmed . Silver prices opened distinctly higher on the back of an overnight spurt in the world market and limited arrivals helped the market extend gains towards the close , dealers said . Silver was down 80 rupees per kg on Wednesday . " Physical buying by industrial consumers remained low today but heavy speculative activity following an upsurge in the world market dragged prices to dizzy heights , " one broker said . " Such a big jump in a single day has been seen after a long time in the silver market , " he added . Silver prices in the world market has gone up from 4 . 83 dollars to 5 . 15 dollars per ounce . 
